  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with combined Anterolateral ligament (ALL) reconstruction- Anterior cruciate
      ligament (ACL) revision will have a better rotational knee stability and therefore better
      patient reported outcome measure (PROM) scores compared to patients, who have ACL revision
      surgery without ALL reconstruction.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
